pr_review_comment_body:
What about the example below? The logic is as before my changes but moved to a separate "builder" function:
```python
def generate_dim_and_axis():
    for ndim in (2, 3):
        for axis in range(ndim):
            yield ndim, axis
dim_axis = list(generate_dim_and_axis())
```
I personally prefer the double comprehension version, but open to change :-)

@jonparrott I think this change broke our auto-release bits:  I just got the following e-mail following @crwilcox's releases:

```bash
# If this is not a CircleCI tag, no-op.
if [[ -z &quot;$CIRCLE_TAG&quot; ]]; then
  echo &quot;This is not a release tag. Doing nothing.&quot;
  exit 0
fi

# H/T: http://stackoverflow.com/a/246128/1068170
SCRIPT=&quot;$(dirname &quot;${BASH_SOURCE[0]}&quot;)/get_tagged_package.py&quot;
dirname &quot;${BASH_SOURCE[0]}&quot;
# Determine the package directory being deploying on this tag.
PKG_DIR=&quot;$(python ${SCRIPT})&quot;
python ${SCRIPT}

# Ensure that we have the latest versions of Twine, Wheel, and Setuptools.
python3 -m pip install --upgrade twine wheel setuptools
/usr/local/bin/python3: No module named pip
Exited with code 1
```

@pedrobaeza 
Do you think that's necessary?

There are plenty of well-former cases, see [here](https://github.com/OCA/pylint-odoo/blob/8845b74/pylint_odoo/test_repo/broken_module/models/broken_model.py#L206-L219). That's the reason why I didn't included them, because they are already covered in the same method.
